what_failed:
Regression (0.11x): ** Combined both time windows into a single query with conditional aggregation. Pre-filtered and cross-joined dimension tables once to create a compact dimension subset before joining with the large fact table.

**Expected speedup:** 2.5x+ due to single fact table scan, reduced join cardinality via pre-filtered dimensions, and elimination of duplicate dimension processing.
why_it_failed: Split a simple OR condition (t_hour BETWEEN 10 AND 11 OR t_hour BETWEEN 16 AND 17) into UNION ALL of two separate web_sales scans. This doubles the fact table scan. DuckDB handles same-column OR ranges efficiently in a single scan — the UNION ALL adds materialization overhead with zero selectivity benefit.
